     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "TransformByFourier[v] is formally equivalent to Fourier[v] but v can be \
a list of non-numeric symbols. If v is a higher dimensional tensor the \
transform is on the last index. TransformByFourier[old \\[RightArrow] new] \
returns a list of Rules that make the discrete Fourier transform. \
TransformByFourier[expr, old \\[RightArrow] new] applies the discrete Fourier \
transformation on expr, which is expressed originally in the operators in the \
list old, to the expression in terms of operators in the list new.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "TransformByFourier", 
